"Communication networks are essential for all areas and sectors of our societies and economies in both developed and emerging countries. Critical infrastructure such as energy, gas, water, transportation and health are becoming increasingly dependent on Internet connectivity. Of the global ICT market of €2646bn, the telecommunications market represents 62% while the general IT market is 38%, highlighting the significance and scale of these sectors. The communication network and service environment of 4G and 5G communications networks will be infinitely richer and more complex than that of today. The future will encompass connected sensors, vehicles, smart meters and smart home gadgets. So there is an urgent need to properly address the novel infrastructure that will be required – and the security implications – as Kashif Faheem and Dr Khalid Rafique explain."
